  "text": "If B = 0, we have an accidental-bequest model. In that case, s * (. , .), and hence b * (. , .), depends upon a but not y. Hence, when B = 0, b * /a is a constant. If B > 0, we have an intentional-bequest model. Even in the latter case, however, (8)- [CITATION_1] show that actual bequests are a mixture of accidental and intentional transfers.",
